                    <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-1">QUICK ANSWER</p>
                    <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>How much does it cost to import chargers from China?</strong> Total landed cost typically adds 25-50% to the factory price. For example, a $10 charger shipped from Shenzhen to a US warehouse costs approximately $12.50-14.00 landed, including duties (7.5-25% Section 301), shipping (15-30% of product cost), and customs broker fees.</p>
